</p>

<p>As for Twitter, with the upcoming <a href="https://twitter.com/TwitterDev/status/1621026986784337922" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">removal of all free API access</a> it likely means the end for Bird Feeder and Tweet Digest. What this means for me is that I’ll most likely stop reading Twitter altogether — I certainly have no interest in using the first-party client with its algorithmic timeline. However, I’ve been enjoying Mastodon more lately anyway (<a href="https://persistent.info/@mihai" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">@mihai@persistent.info</a> should find me), and with being able to consume⁴ it in my feed reader, it’s truly more than a 1:1 replacement for Twitter.</p>

