<li>Technically Atom feeds, but I’ve decided to use the term RSS generically since it’s not 2004 anymore.</li>
<li>My dilly-dallying until I settled on <a href="https://hachyderm.io/home" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">hachyderm.io</a> mean that someone else <a href="https://hachyderm.io/@mihai" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">got @mihai</a> a few days before <a href="https://hachyderm.io/@mihaip" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">I signed up</a>.</li>
<li>It did pain me to have to write a bunch more Python 2.7 code that will eventually <a href="https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/standard/lifecycle/support-schedule#python" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">be unsupported</a>, but that’s a future Mihai problem.</li>
<li>For posting I end up using the built-in web UI on desktop, or <a href="https://tapbots.com/ivory/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Ivory</a> on my iPhone and iPad. <a href="https://www.opener.link/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Opener</a> is also handy when I want to open a specific post from NetNewsWire in Ivory (e.g. to reply to it).</li>
